<font color="#FF0000">SPIT ON SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jul 20 23:31:19 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I find it impossible to refer to this foul mouthed idiot as a doctor, but it is not difficult to figure him out.  He is a prisoner of the pleasure principle.  Totally without critical, internalized values, he cannot subscribe to the disciplines of loyality, courage, delay of gratification or any other values that serve to help individuals self regiment their lives.  He reacts to external rules and disciplines with contempt and fear, because he did not acquire appreciable boundaries as a developing human.  He has no rules for himself, therefore he has no respect for the rules of others.  He is a predator in a free society, a parasite preying upon the fruits of others' labor and sacrifice.  It is understandable that he wants to be accepted.  Psychological defense mechanisms lead him to justify his cowardice.  He conjurs up this idea that war is wrong and therefore he is excused.  Any idot knows that war is wrong.  No one hates war more than those who have experienced it first hand.<br>
I do not perceive him as a patriot, seeking government reform, trying to save the lives of young soldiers or having any acceptable motive.  Instead, I see him as a gutless, terrorfied, insecure weakling, clamoring to recover a long lost or never attained self dignity.  In anger and frustration he opts to chastize those who did what he should have done.  He chooses to find contempt for the achiever rather than recognize his own frailty.  Unabated, his filthy mouth spews forth an avalance of ridiculous rhetoric, behind which, he hides his shame.<br>
However, I commend him for his prudence in assailing combat veterans electronically instead of face to face, otherwise, someone would have solved his problem a long time ago.  I have compassion for this jerk who is actively seeking a masculine identity; I appreciate his not spitting on returning veterans... still, I would greatly relish the act of spitting in his face.<br><br>
For your information, Spatz... I am a veteran of two tours of intensive combat in Viet Nam.  I respect those who oppose war for many viable reasons, which do not include the immoral and unrestrained pursuit of pleasure which emanates from a drugged stupor or denied cowardice.  I hope your obscene mind can interrogate the ultimate insult in something short of filthy language.<br>
I cannot think of anything that I hate more than war... the conduct of it, the consequences and aftermath, the memories of it or the realization of the political and economic motives that placed us in Viet Nam, but you come a close second.<br><br>

